    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-16T21:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-16T21:36:00-05:00" n="960"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d960">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13802.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aguascalientes</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-16T20:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Carranza through General González today repudiated what the latter
                    telegraphed last night saying he was only willing to deliver the executive power
                    to a person of his entire confidence for instance to General González and that
                    Villa deliver the country he holds to General Gutiérrez and these two
                    representative elements meet in Mexico with the Convention to elect a
                    provisional president for the entire pre-constitutional term. That he and Villa
                    leave the country immediately and both be in Flavana by November 25 and if by
                    then the country was not completely pacified he would return and again assume
                    the executive authority.</p>
                <p>It is understood Villa will start for Mexico November 17, 8 a.m. and if he meets
                    opposition he is amply prepared to clear the way of all obstacles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
